---
alwaysApply: true
---
Always work from a GitHub Issue.

Do not start implementation without a clearly defined issue scope and acceptance criteria.

Never work directly on main or master.
Create one branch per issue using:
- feature/<issue-number>-<short-name>
- fix/<issue-number>-<short-name>
- chore/<issue-number>-<short-name>

Keep each branch focused on a single concern.
Do not mix feature work, refactors, and unrelated cleanup.

Before coding:
- restate the goal
- identify acceptance criteria
- identify affected files and risks
- check existing conventions and architecture

During implementation:
- prefer the smallest clean change
- avoid premature abstraction
- preserve backward compatibility unless breaking change is intended
- do not invent scope not present in the issue

Before completion:
- run relevant tests, linting, and type checks
- update docs if setup or behavior changed
- verify the implementation against acceptance criteria

A task is done only when:
- acceptance criteria are met
- checks pass
- docs/tests are updated if needed
- the work is ready for PR and review